Bears also have died after being shot by hunters claiming self-defense or saying they mistook a grizzly for a black bear.
Grizzly bears in Yellowstone National Park can weigh up to 600 pounds.
Female grizzlies mate only every second or third year.
Only 200 or 250 grizzlies were in that region in 1975, when grizzly bears in the lower 48 states were listed under the Endangered Species Act.
Chris Servheen, grizzly bear recovery coordinator for the Fish and Wildlife Service, said he also supported taking bears off the list.
Alaskan grizzly bears, which number around 30,000, were never listed under the act.
